The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Top-level Lever reshuffle

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, May 15: Hindustan Lever Ltd today said it had inducted new officials into its management committee.

 The appointments come into effect from June 1.

 Sales and customer development executive director Sanjay Dube has been appointed chairman for the Poland and Baltics market.

 Marketing and strategy (foods) executive director Sanjiv Kakkar will succeed Dube, a company release said.

 Vice-president (legal) Ashok Gupta has been made executive director. He will take over M.K. Sharmas place in the committee. Sharma is retiring on May 31.

 Vice-president (HR) Leena Nair joins the list of new executive directors and finds a place in the management committee.




